Hi,
I am a student at the School of Mines. I am working on modeling a fuel cell with
Cantera. I am trying to use Cantera to calculate fluxes through a porous media.
I am trying to use the function getMolarFluxes from the DustyGasTransport
class, but everytime the program runs I get an error that stops the program. I
first declared the Thermo Phase object for the gas. Then set the parameters for
the porous material. Then declare the state of the gas. Then call the function
getMolarFluxes. Is there a step I am missing. Any hints. I have tried declaring
the state and not declaring the state before trying to find the fluxes.
Thank You
Andrew
